sf_description: verage number of requests received by each target in a target group. You must specify the target group using the TargetGroup dimension
Number of requests processed over IPv4 and IPv6. This count includes only the requests with a response generated by a target of the load balancer.
Total number of concurrent TCP connections active from clients to the load balancer and from the load balancer to targets.

sf_chart: Target TLS Negotiation Error Count per sec
sf_description: Number of TLS connections initiated by the load balancer that did not establish a session with the target. Possible causes include a mismatch of ciphers or protocols.
Number of load balancer capacity units (LCU) used by your load balancer. You pay for the number of LCUs that you use per hour.

sf_chart: Client TLS Negotiation Error Count per sec
sf_description: Number of TLS connections initiated by the client that did not establish a session with the load balancer. Possible causes include a mismatch of ciphers or protocols.
Total number of new TCP connections established from clients to the load balancer and from the load balancer to targets.
Number of connections that were not successfully established between the load balancer and target.
The total number of bytes processed by the load balancer over IPv4 and IPv6.
The time elapsed, in seconds, after the request leaves the load balancer until a response from the target is received. This is equivalent to the target_processing_time field in the access logs.

sf_chart: HTTP Result Codes/min from load balancer
sf_description: Number of HTTP error codes that originate from the load balancer. These requests have not been received by the target. This count does not include any response codes generated by the targets.
